HEADWORD: Ambiparous
<hw>Am*bip"a*rous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ambo</ets> both + <ets>parere</ets> to bring forth.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Characterized by containing the rudiments of both
flowers and leaves; -- applied to a bud.</def>⟦br⟧
